│ THOUGHT: Now I understand the issue better. The `createShuffle` method in `BaseShuffleAnalysis` calls `Builder.createShuffleVector` which creates the actual shufflevector instruction. The problem is that    │
│ when creating a shufflevector that uses values from other vector operations (like the OR instruction), those other instructions need to be created first.                                                      │
